"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(DISTINCT e.ID)\nFROM Examination e\nJOIN Patient p ON e.ID = p.ID\nWHERE e.Thrombosis = 1\n  AND YEAR(e.`Examination Date`) = 1997\n  AND p.SEX = 'F';\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of distinct female patients (`SEX = 'F'`) who had the most serious thrombosis cases (`Thrombosis = 1`) examined in the year 1997. It joins the `Examination` and `Patient` tables using the foreign key relationship between `Examination.ID` and `Patient.ID`."